    <summary>Automated Spectrum-Based Fault Localization for Java</summary>
    <description>
Javelin CLI is an automated spectrum-based fault localization (SBFL) tool for Java projects.
It supports Ochiai and Ochiai-MS algorithms to rank suspicious lines of code based on test pass/fail data.

## Features

- **Ochiai SBFL** — Standard spectrum-based fault localization
- **Ochiai-MS (Experimental)** — Mutation score–weighted SBFL using PITest
- **JaCoCo integration** — Automatic coverage instrumentation
- **Parallel test execution** — Configurable thread count
- **CSV output** — Ranked suspiciousness report

## Requirements

- Java 21 or later (any vendor: Temurin, Oracle, Corretto, GraalVM, etc.)

## Notes

This is a pre-release build for early testing. The Ochiai-MS algorithm is experimental.
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/DesmondQue/javelin-cli/releases/tag/v1.0.0-beta</releaseNotes>
